{"title_page": "Gura Cali\u021bei", "text_new": "{{Infobox Romanian subdivision\n|type                   = commune\n|county                 = Vrancea\n|population_total       = auto\n|map_caption            = Location in Vrancea County\n|name=Gura Cali\u021bei\n|image_map              = Gura Calitei jud Vrancea.png\n|coordinates = {{coord|45|35|N|27|1|E|region:RO|display=it}}\n}}\n'''Gura Cali\u021bei''' is a [[Commune in Romania|commune]] located in [[Vrancea County]], [[Romania]]. It is composed of ten villages: B\u0103l\u0103ne\u0219ti, Coco\u0219ari, Dealu Lung, Groapa Tufei, Gura Cali\u021bei, Lacu lui Baban, Plopu, Poenile, Ra\u0219ca and \u0218ot\u00e2rcari.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Vrancea County}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gura Calitei}}\n[[Category:Communes in Vrancea County]]\n[[Category:Localities in Muntenia]]\n\n{{Vrancea-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Romanian subdivision\n|type                   = commune\n|county                 = Vrancea\n|population_total       = auto\n|map_caption            = Location in Vrancea County\n|name=Gura Cali\u021bei\n|image_map=\n|coordinates = {{coord|45|35|N|27|1|E|region:RO|display=it}}\n}}\n'''Gura Cali\u021bei''' is a [[Commune in Romania|commune]] located in [[Vrancea County]], [[Romania]]. It is composed of ten villages: B\u0103l\u0103ne\u0219ti, Coco\u0219ari, Dealu Lung, Groapa Tufei, Gura Cali\u021bei, Lacu lui Baban, Plopu, Poenile, Ra\u0219ca and \u0218ot\u00e2rcari.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Vrancea County}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gura Calitei}}\n[[Category:Communes in Vrancea County]]\n[[Category:Localities in Muntenia]]\n\n{{Vrancea-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Markussep", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gura_Cali%C8%9Bei"}
{"title_page": "Ben Carroll", "text_new": "{{short description|Australian politician|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2014}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=June 2014}}\n{{Infobox AM\n| honorific-prefix    = [[The Honourable]]\n| name                = Ben Carroll\n| honorific-suffix    = [[Victorian Legislative Assembly|MP]]\n| image               = [[File:CarrollBenjaminAlan 108.jpg|frameless|Parliament photo]]\n| alt                 = \n| caption             = \n| office              = Minister for Industry and Employment\n| term_start          = 16 October 2017\n| term_end            = \n| predecessor         = [[Wade Noonan]]\n| constituency_AM1    = [[Electoral district of Niddrie|Niddrie]]\n| assembly1           = Victorian Legislative\n| term_start1         = 24 March 2012\n| term_end1           = \n| predecessor1        = [[Rob Hulls]]\n| successor1          = \n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1975|7|12}}\n| birth_place         = [[Coburg, Victoria|Coburg]], [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], [[Australia]]\n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| restingplace        = \n| restingplacecoordinates = \n| birthname           = Benjamin Alan Carroll\n| citizenship         = \n| nationality         = Australian\n| party               = [[Australian Labor Party (Victorian Branch)|Labor Party]]\n| spouse              = \n| partner             = <!--For those with a domestic partner and not married-->\n| relations           = \n| children            = \n| residence           = \n| alma_mater          = [[La Trobe University]]\n| occupation          = Politician\n| profession          = Lawyer\n| cabinet             = \n| committees          = \n| portfolio           = \n| religion            = \n| signature           = \n| signature_alt       = \n| website             = http://www.bencarroll.com.au\n}}\n'''Benjamin Alan Carroll''' (born 12 July 1975) is an Australian politician. He is the representative for the seat of [[Electoral district of Niddrie|Niddrie]] in the [[Victorian Legislative Assembly]].\n\n==Early years and education==\n\nBen was born in [[Airport West, Victoria]].<ref>Lucas, Clay: [http://www.theage.com.au/victoria/niddrie-at-least-swings-labors-way-20120325-1vsia.html Niddrie, at least, swings Labor's way], ''The Age'', 26 March 2012.</ref> He attended primary school at St Christopher's Primary, and high school at St Bernard's College. He then studied law at [[La Trobe University]], graduating with honours in 2000. He was admitted as a legal solicitor in 2010. He holds a masters in law from La Trobe, having commenced the degree subsequent to his 2012 election. \n\nPrior to entering politics Ben worked as a sales assistant for [[Kmart Australia|Kmart]], and for the insurance company [[AAMI]] in its motor vehicles division. He also worked for the [[Solicitor-General of Victoria|Victorian Government Solicitor]] between 2009 and 2010.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.parliament.vic.gov.au/about/people-in-parliament/members-search/search-members/details/22/108|title=Member Profile - The Hon. Ben Carroll|website=www.parliament.vic.gov.au|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n==Political Career==\nBen Carroll has worked as a political adviser to adviser to [[Steve Bracks]], [[Justin Madden]], and [[Stephen Conroy]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIn 2012, Carroll was elected to the seat of [[Electoral district of Niddrie|Niddrie]] in a by-election following the resignation of [[Rob Hulls]]. He was re-elected in 2014, and 2018 for the seat.\n\nHe was appointed Parliamentary Secretary for Justice in the Andrews Labor Government in December 2014. In October 2017, Carroll was appointed Minister for Industry and Employment, after the resignation of [[Wade Noonan]] from cabinet.<ref name=\"minister\">{{cite news|last1=Carey|first1=Adam|title=Ben Carroll joins Andrews' cabinet to take on key employment ministry|url=https://www.theage.com.au/national/victoria/reshuffle-looms-as-ben-carroll-joins-andrews-cabinet-to-replace-wade-noonan-20171016-gz1nc7.html|accessdate=29 March 2018|work=The Age|date=16 October 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://vicvote.review/assembly/members/Ben%20Carroll.html Parliamentary voting record of Ben Carroll at Victorian Parliament Tracker]\n* [http://www.parliament.vic.gov.au/members/id/1729 Parliament of Victoria: Members Information]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|au-vic-la}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Rob Hulls]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member for [[Electoral district of Niddrie|Niddrie]]|years=2012\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Wade Noonan]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Minister for Industry and Employment|years=2017\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Cabinet of Victoria}}\n{{VicCurrentMLAs}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Carroll, Ben}}\n[[Category:1975 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Members of the Victorian Legislative Assembly]]\n[[Category:La Trobe University alumni]]\n[[Category:Australian Labor Party members of the Parliament of Victoria]]\n[[Category:Labor Right politicians]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Melbourne]]\n[[Category:21st-century Australian politicians]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Australian politician|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2014}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=June 2014}}\n{{Infobox AM\n| honorific-prefix    = [[The Honourable]]\n| name                = Ben Carroll\n| honorific-suffix    = [[Victorian Legislative Assembly|MP]]\n| image               = [[File:CarrollBenjaminAlan 108.jpg|frameless|Parliament photo]]\n| alt                 = \n| caption             = \n| office              = Minister for Industry and Employment\n| term_start          = 16 October 2017\n| term_end            = \n| predecessor         = [[Wade Noonan]]\n| constituency_AM1    = [[Electoral district of Niddrie|Niddrie]]\n| assembly1           = Victorian Legislative\n| term_start1         = 24 March 2012\n| term_end1           = \n| predecessor1        = [[Rob Hulls]]\n| successor1          = \n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1975|7|12}}\n| birth_place         = [[Coburg, Victoria|Coburg]], [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], [[Australia]]\n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| restingplace        = \n| restingplacecoordinates = \n| birthname           = Benjamin Alan Carroll\n| citizenship         = \n| nationality         = Australian\n| party               = [[Australian Labor Party (Victorian Branch)|Labor Party]]\n| spouse              = \n| partner             = <!--For those with a domestic partner and not married-->\n| relations           = \n| children            = \n| residence           = \n| alma_mater          = [[La Trobe University]]\n| occupation          = Politician\n| profession          = Lawyer\n| cabinet             = \n| committees          = \n| portfolio           = \n| religion            = \n| signature           = \n| signature_alt       = \n| website             = http://www.bencarroll.com.au\n}}\n'''Benjamin Alan Carroll''' (born 12 July 1975) is an Australian politician. He is the representative for the seat of [[Electoral district of Niddrie|Niddrie]] in the [[Victorian Legislative Assembly]].\n\n==Early years and education==\n\nBen was born in [[Airport West, Victoria]].<ref>Lucas, Clay: [http://www.theage.com.au/victoria/niddrie-at-least-swings-labors-way-20120325-1vsia.html Niddrie, at least, swings Labor's way], ''The Age'', 26 March 2012.</ref> He attended primary school at St Christopher's Primary, and high school at St Bernard's College. He then studied law at [[La Trobe University]], graduating with honours in 2000. He was admitted as a legal solicitor in 2010. He holds a masters in law from La Trobe, having commenced the degree subsequent to his 2012 election. \n\nPrior to entering politics Ben worked as a sales assistant for [[Kmart Australia|Kmart]], and for the insurance company [[AAMI]] in its motor vehicles division. He also worked for the [[Solicitor-General of Victoria|Victorian Government Solicitor]] between 2009 and 2010.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.parliament.vic.gov.au/about/people-in-parliament/members-search/search-members/details/22/108|title=Member Profile - The Hon. Ben Carroll|website=www.parliament.vic.gov.au|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n==Political Career==\nBen Carroll has worked as a political adviser to adviser to [[Steve Bracks]], [[Justin Madden]], and [[Stephen Conroy]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIn 2012, Carroll was elected to the seat of [[Electoral district of Niddrie|Niddrie]] in a by-election following the resignation of [[Rob Hulls]]. He was re-elected in 2014, and 2018 for the seat.\n\nHe was appointed Parliamentary Secretary for Justice in the Andrews Labor Government in December 2014. In October 2017, Carroll was appointed Minister for Industry and Employment, after the resignation of [[Wade Noonan]] from cabinet.<ref name=\"minister\">{{cite news|last1=Carey|first1=Adam|title=Ben Carroll joins Andrews' cabinet to take on key employment ministry|url=https://www.theage.com.au/national/victoria/reshuffle-looms-as-ben-carroll-joins-andrews-cabinet-to-replace-wade-noonan-20171016-gz1nc7.html|accessdate=29 March 2018|work=The Age|date=16 October 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://vicvote.review/assembly/members/Ben%20Carroll.html Parliamentary voting record of Ben Carroll at Victorian Parliament Tracker]\n* [http://www.parliament.vic.gov.au/members/id/1729 Parliament of Victoria: Members Information]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|au-vic-la}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Rob Hulls]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member for [[Electoral district of Niddrie|Niddrie]]|years=2012\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Wade Noonan]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Minister for Industry and Employment|years=2017\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Cabinet of Victoria}}\n{{VicCurrentMLAs}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Carroll, Ben}}